{"type":"message","id":"b09edaf5","parentId":"82d6973e","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:45:23.859Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-09 19:45 EST] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: # TASK: Fix LPO Skill Recommendation Logic\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe `long-prompt-orchestrator` skill has a critical defect in its skill recommendation logic:\n\n**PROBLEM**: LPO incorrectly recommends `salesforce-code-auditor` for NON-Salesforce tasks.\n\n**EVIDENCE FROM REAL TEST**:\n- Prompt: \"Inventory workspace skills and check system health\"\n- LPO recommendation: `salesforce-code-auditor` ❌ (INCORRECTO)\n- Correct skill: Should be `workspace-janitor` or direct main agent execution\n\n**IMPACT**: This prevents testing of real delegation to sub-agents because wrong skills are recommended.\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nFix the skill recommendation logic in LPO to correctly match tasks to appropriate skills.\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Analyze Current Defect\nExamine `plan_generator.py` to understand why it defaults to `salesforce-code-auditor`.\n\n### 2. Implement Better Skill Matching\nCreate intelligent skill matching based on:\n- **Task keywords**: \"inventory\", \"audit\", \"analyze\", \"research\", \"check\", \"monitor\"\n- **Task domain**: Salesforce, workspace, system, web, memory, errors\n- **Available skills**: Map task types to appropriate skills\n\n### 3. Skill Matching Rules Required\n\n#### For NON-Salesforce tasks:\n- \"inventory workspace\" → `workspace-janitor` or direct main execution\n- \"check system health\" → direct main execution or `agent-watchdog`\n- \"research [topic]\" → `tavily-web-search`\n- \"analyze memory\" → `vector-memory`\n- \"handle errors\" → `error-learning-loop`\n- \"orchestrate/decompose\" → `long-prompt-orchestrator` (self-reference)\n\n#### For Salesforce tasks:\n- \"salesforce audit\" → `salesforce-code-auditor`\n- \"salesforce architecture\" → `salesforce-architect`\n- \"apex/lwc analysis\" → `salesforce-code-auditor`\n\n### 4. Fix Implementation Points\n1. **`plan_generator.py`** - Skill recommendation logic\n2. **Task classification system** - Better task type detection\n3. **Skill mapping configuration** - Configurable skill-task mappings\n\n### 5. Testing Requirements\nCreate tests that prove:\n- Correct skill recommendations for various task types\n- No more incorrect `salesforce-code-auditor` recommendations for non-Salesforce tasks\n- Real delegation can now be tested\n\n## ANTI-SIMULATION RULES\n- NO placeholder fixes\n- REAL code changes required\n- REAL test evidence required\n- NO \"would work\" documentation-only fixes\n\n## DELIVERABLES\n1. **Fixed `plan_generator.py`** with corrected skill recommendation logic\n2. **Test evidence** showing:\n   - Before: Incorrect `salesforce-code-auditor` recommendation\n   - After: Correct skill recommendations for various task types\n   - Real delegation now possible\n3. **Updated documentation** reflecting fixed logic\n4. **Handoff report** with fix evidence\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\nLPO skill recommendation is **FIXED** when:\n1. No more incorrect `salesforce-code-auditor` recommendations for non-Salesforce tasks\n2. Tasks are matched to appropriate skills based on content\n3. Real delegation to sub-agents can be tested\n4. Evidence shows corrected behavior\n\n## FAILURE CRITERIA\nFix is **NOT COMPLETE** if:\n1. `salesforce-code-auditor` still recommended for non-Salesforce tasks\n2. Skill matching is still broken\n3. No real test evidence provided\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 20 minutes\n- Report: Concise handoff with fix evidence\n\nProceed to fix this critical defect in LPO skill recommendation logic."}],"timestamp":1773103523857}}
