{"type":"message","id":"27d0c5c1","parentId":"e10c2ddb","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:53:40.507Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the SKILL.md file to see if it needs updating:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_7Y6GiMtHyQ0e1wYOa7Yzh0BP","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/SKILL.md","limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":278,"output":94,"cacheRead":44800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45172,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773104015470}}
{"type":"message","id":"375e07e6","parentId":"27d0c5c1","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:53:40.548Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_7Y6GiMtHyQ0e1wYOa7Yzh0BP","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: long-prompt-orchestrator\ndescription: A production-ready Long Prompt Planner that automatically decomposes overly long/complex tasks into structured plans for main agent execution. Generates task DAGs with dependencies, resource estimates, and execution recommendations. Does NOT execute tasks or spawn sub-agents.\ncategory: planning\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"python\", \"workspace_write\"]\noptional_requires: [\"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: false\n---\n\n# long-prompt-orchestrator\n\n## Purpose\nAutomatically detect overly long prompts or complex tasks, decompose them into smaller dependent tasks, and generate structured execution plans for the main agent. The skill provides comprehensive planning including task dependencies, resource estimates, skill recommendations, and execution strategies. Main agent uses these plans to spawn and coordinate sub-agents.\n\n## CORRECTED ARCHITECTURE (IMPORTANT)\n**This skill ONLY generates plans. It does NOT execute tasks or spawn sub-agents.**\n\n### Role Clarification:\n- ✅ **Skill Responsibility**: Planning, decomposition, resource estimation, dependency analysis\n- ✅ **Main Agent Responsibility**: Spawning sub-agents, execution coordination, validation, synthesis\n- ❌ **Skill DOES NOT**: Execute tasks, spawn sub-agents, track execution state, validate outputs\n\n### Key Changes:\n1. **Removed all spawning code** - Skill cannot spawn sub-agents from Python\n2. **Added plan generation** - Outputs structured JSON plans for main agent\n3. **Enhanced task analysis** - Better recommendations for skill/model selection\n4. **Updated documentation** - Clear separation of responsibilities\n\n## When to Use\n- When the main agent receives a prompt that is too long (estimated tokens > 4000)\n- When a task appears complex: expected steps > 5, multi‑file outputs, multi‑agent operations, long tool execution sequences\n- When you need to split a large task into manageable sub‑tasks with dependencies\n- When you need a structured execution plan for distributed workflow\n\n## When NOT to Use\n- For simple, short prompts (estimated tokens < 1000)\n- For tasks that require atomic, non‑decomposable execution\n- When the user explicitly wants a single‑step response\n- When the task is already being handled by another planning/orchestration skill\n- **When you need task execution** (use main agent with generated plan instead)\n\n## Inputs\n- Original prompt (string)\n- Optional configuration (MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS, MAX_MINI_TASKS, etc.)\n- Optional checkpoint/task_id for recovery\n\n## Outputs\n\n[331 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773104020537}}
